TITLE: Hamas attack evokes memories of the Holocaust for many Jews
SUMMARY: The deadly assault in Israel has been compared to the Nazis’ genocide of 6 million Jews. But there is disagreement about invoking that epochal evil in the context of a military campaign

TITLE: Travis King, U.S. soldier who ran into North Korea, is charged with desertion
SUMMARY: The eight counts against King, a soldier stationed in South Korea who fled across a fortified border to the North, also involve child pornography and the assault of fellow soldiers

TITLE: China is building up its nuclear arsenal faster than predicted, U.S. report says
SUMMARY: The Pentagon report also warned that Beijing may be pursuing a new intercontinental missile system that could allow it to threaten conventional strikes against targets in the U.S

TITLE: Massive protests seen at U.S. embassies in several countries after Gaza hospital bombing
SUMMARY: Thousands marched in big cities across the world expressing their support for Palestinians and their frustrations with the U.S. and Israel

TITLE: Israeli family fears child may spend his 9th birthday as a hostage of Hamas
SUMMARY: Osnat Meiri, 53, said she feared her nephew Ohad had lost his glasses and would not be able to see

TITLE: As Israel-Hamas war rages, a school blast shows people in Gaza have nowhere to run
SUMMARY: Following evacuation orders from the north, fleeing Palestinians are met with more danger in the south

TITLE: London police offer new reward in cold case of body discovered in wine bar freezer after 9 years
SUMMARY: Roy Bigg’s body was discovered on Oct. 15, 2021, in the basement of a building that was once a wine bar. He went missing in February 2012, according to the Metropolitan Police Service

TITLE: Central America scrambles without international solution to record migration
SUMMARY: Regional leaders will seek longer term solutions at an upcoming migration summit on Sunday in Mexico

TITLE: Iran is not currently seeking direct war with United States, U.S. officials say
SUMMARY: But provocative actions by Iran’s proxies in the region are raising the danger of miscalculation and an unintended war, sources say

TITLE: What is Hamas? What to know about the group behind the deadly terror attack in Israel
SUMMARY: A once-obscure militant group founded more than 35 years ago in Gaza has killed 900 Israelis and taken dozens of civilians and soldiers hostage
